RT: Using citizen science data collected from over 4000 dogs: all breeds, regardless of size or lifespan, tend to follow similar cognitive aging trajectories. This means that larger dogs, with often shorter lifespans, may experience limited cognitive decline. https://t.co/Er6XPTqh9N

RT: Citizen science boundaries are fuzzy - deciding what is in and what is out depends on context, on the scientific area, on the financial relationships between the person who participate and the body that coordinates and run the project. And other things, of course. Tricky!

RT: But in many cases, people need definitions - for example, in setting policy that supports citizen science, or in calls for funding. Or if you are a researcher or participants who want to know if what you?re involved in deserves to be called citizen science. 6/15

RT: Apa itu Citizen Science? 
 
 Rakyat terlibat dalam ujikaji dan pengumpulan data bagi meningkatkan ilmu dalam penyelidikan. Konsep ini sudah lama & merupakan sebahagian daripada ekosistem Open Science. 
 
 NASA antara terawal guna konsep ini untuk tingkatkan penyelidikan mereka https://t.co/noNQqMMwey

Citizen science boundaries are fuzzy - deciding what is in and what is out depends on context, on the scientific area, on the financial relationships between the person who participate and the body that coordinates and run the project. And other things, of course. Tricky!
